ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I got along with this doctor.
The doctor explained things s/he did to me during the checkup.
I could talk to the doctor like a friend.
This doctor helped me learn how to take care of myself.
The doctor let me say how I felt about the things s/he did to me.
This doctor knows what it's like to be my age.
This doctor understood what I was trying to say.
The doctor asked me questions about the things I like to do.
The doctor explained things so I could remember them.
The doctor I just saw cared about how I felt.
The doctor I saw today helped me feel calm.
When I was done seeing the doctor, I felt better about my health.
